cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a probabilistic robustness measure for Bayesian Neural Networks (BNNs) and develops a framework to estimate probabilistic robustness with statistical guarantees. It also compares several approximate BNN inference techniques on image classification tasks. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with adversarial examples and uncertainty in BNN predictions, which are important topics in AI research. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image classification tasks. 

It may also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the probability of the existence of adversarial examples and the quantification of uncertainty in adversarial settings. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with Bayesian Neural Networks and their robustness.
